* Iron had moved back a second after she had strick, out of arms reach of 
Marine. To remain close after striking was asking for damage. But her 
attacks were quick before she moved off to decide where to attack next, 
always moving in for the kill and then out to save on damage. The taste of 
his mech fluid was fresh in her mouth and pieces of Marine's armor were 
stuck between her teeth, though the piece she had torn from him had been 
quickly swollowed.
Her SBM thrived off of the energy of other robotics, which was a stable 
diet. Meat wasn't a favorite, but curcuits were.
IR was about to sweep in behind Marine and go at his back when she suddenly 
smelled something different, though the smell of mech fluid almost swamped 
her senses. Her head swept up and over Mariens, turning to look behind her 
just in time to see Ominous Prime and Quasar.
A loud roar/hiss erupted from her throat as she brought her head back and 
then snapped it forward, sending a large spray of yellow acid at them. But 
she hadn't moved while attacking so 12 of the energy shots sent by those two 
hit dead on, though 4 only skidded along her sides and back before 
continuing on to explode in the ground, but left deep gashes in their wake.
Iron screamed and hissed, turning around again to glare at Marine, 
explosings erupting from behind, armor/skin peeling back to expose curcuits 
inside. Damage had been given. Since the damage was to her back quarters, 
her hips were the first things to be effected and her legs collapsed but not 
before she spat a thick layer of acit at Marine.
But then something caught her eye, only proped up by her front limbs, she 
swung her head around and looked at Jackle. His shots leveled her, chin 
slamming against the ground with a grunt but not before she slashed her tail 
at Ominous and Quasar.*
